# 🔍 DETECTIONS (1–10)

---

# 🔥 Detection #1 — Successful Logon Monitoring

## Objective
Detect successful authentication events on the system.

## Event ID
- 4624

## Analysis
Captured successful logon activity including:
- Username
- Logon type
- Source machine
- Authentication context

## MITRE Mapping
- T1078 — Valid Accounts

---

# 🔥 Detection #2 — Failed Logon Attempts

## Objective
Detect incorrect or malicious login attempts.

## Event ID
- 4625

## Analysis
Used to identify:
- brute-force attempts
- password guessing activity
- authentication failures

## MITRE Mapping
- T1110 — Brute Force

---

# 🔥 Detection #3 — User Account Creation

## Objective
Detect creation of new local users.

## Event ID
- 4720

## Analysis
Used for detecting:
- persistence mechanisms
- unauthorized account creation

## MITRE Mapping
- T1136 — Create Account

---

# 🔥 Detection #4 — Privilege Escalation (Group Membership Change)

## Objective
Detect users added to privileged groups.

## Event ID
- 4732

## Analysis
Captured:
- user added to administrators group
- identity-based privilege escalation

## MITRE Mapping
- T1068 — Privilege Escalation
- T1078 — Valid Accounts

